{
  "text": "There are approximately 27 studies involving more than 25,000 patients with tetanus over a 60-year period issued from the African continent [CITATION_1] . Most of the reported studies have been done at tertiary level health facilities, similar to our hospital. The median age, male predominance, median time to presentation, clinical presentation, and hospital lengths of stay are similar between our two groups and also similar to other studies of tetanus patients in Africa [CITATION_2] . Most of the studies reported similar high overall hospital fatalities [CITATION_3] . All of this suggests that our hospital setting is similar to many others in sub-Saharan Africa and that our finding that tetanus protocol implementation did not improve mortality is likely to be generalizable as well.",
